HEADWORD: Leucophyll
<hw>Leu"co*phyll</hw> <pr>(l⟦umac⟧"k⟦osl⟧*f⟦icr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Leuco-</ets> + Gr. <grk>fy`llon</grk> a leaf.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A colorless substance isomeric with chlorophyll,
contained in parts of plants capable of becoming green.</def>
<rj><au>Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

